{
    "surah":  79,
    "name_ar":  "سُورَةُ النَّازِعَاتِ",
    "name_en":  "Those who drag forth",
    "revelation":  "Meccan",
    "verses":  [
                   {
                       "ayah":  1,
                       "arabic":  "بِسْمِ ٱللَّهِ ٱلرَّحْمَٰنِ ٱلرَّحِيمِ وَٱلنَّٰزِعَٰتِ غَرْقًۭا",
                       "english":  "By those [angels] who extract with violence"
                   },
                   {
                       "ayah":  2,
                       "arabic":  "وَٱلنَّٰشِطَٰتِ نَشْطًۭا",
                       "english":  "And [by] those who remove with ease"
                   },
                   {
                       "ayah":  3,
                       "arabic":  "وَٱلسَّٰبِحَٰتِ سَبْحًۭا",
                       "english":  "And [by] those who glide [as if] swimming"
                   },
                   {
                       "ayah":  4,
                       "arabic":  "فَٱلسَّٰبِقَٰتِ سَبْقًۭا",
                       "english":  "And those who race each other in a race"
                   },
                   {
                       "ayah":  5,
                       "arabic":  "فَٱلْمُدَبِّرَٰتِ أَمْرًۭا",
                       "english":  "And those who arrange [each] matter,"
                   },
                   {
                       "ayah":  6,
                       "arabic":  "يَوْمَ تَرْجُفُ ٱلرَّاجِفَةُ",
                       "english":  "On the Day the blast [of the Horn] will convulse [creation],"
                   },
                   {
                       "ayah":  7,
                       "arabic":  "تَتْبَعُهَا ٱلرَّادِفَةُ",
                       "english":  "There will follow it the subsequent [one]."
                   },
                   {
                       "ayah":  8,
                       "arabic":  "قُلُوبٌۭ يَوْمَئِذٍۢ وَاجِفَةٌ",
                       "english":  "Hearts, that Day, will tremble,"
                   },
                   {
                       "ayah":  9,
                       "arabic":  "أَبْصَٰرُهَا خَٰشِعَةٌۭ",
                       "english":  "Their eyes humbled."
                   },
                   {
                       "ayah":  10,
                       "arabic":  "يَقُولُونَ أَءِنَّا لَمَرْدُودُونَ فِى ٱلْحَافِرَةِ",
                       "english":  "They are [presently] saying, \"Will we indeed be returned to [our] former state [of life]?"
                   },
                   {
                       "ayah":  11,
                       "arabic":  "أَءِذَا كُنَّا عِظَٰمًۭا نَّخِرَةًۭ",
                       "english":  "Even if we should be decayed bones?"
                   },
                   {
                       "ayah":  12,
                       "arabic":  "قَالُوا۟ تِلْكَ إِذًۭا كَرَّةٌ خَاسِرَةٌۭ",
                       "english":  "They say, \"That, then, would be a losing return.\""
                   },
                   {
                       "ayah":  13,
                       "arabic":  "فَإِنَّمَا هِىَ زَجْرَةٌۭ وَٰحِدَةٌۭ",
                       "english":  "Indeed, it will be but one shout,"
                   },
                   {
                       "ayah":  14,
                       "arabic":  "فَإِذَا هُم بِٱلسَّاهِرَةِ",
                       "english":  "And suddenly they will be [alert] upon the earth\u0027s surface."
                   },
                   {
                       "ayah":  15,
                       "arabic":  "هَلْ أَتَىٰكَ حَدِيثُ مُوسَىٰٓ",
                       "english":  "Has there reached you the story of Moses? -"
                   },
                   {
                       "ayah":  16,
                       "arabic":  "إِذْ نَادَىٰهُ رَبُّهُۥ بِٱلْوَادِ ٱلْمُقَدَّسِ طُوًى",
                       "english":  "When his Lord called to him in the sacred valley of Tuwa,"
                   },
                   {
                       "ayah":  17,
                       "arabic":  "ٱذْهَبْ إِلَىٰ فِرْعَوْنَ إِنَّهُۥ طَغَىٰ",
                       "english":  "\"Go to Pharaoh. Indeed, he has transgressed."
                   },
                   {
                       "ayah":  18,
                       "arabic":  "فَقُلْ هَل لَّكَ إِلَىٰٓ أَن تَزَكَّىٰ",
                       "english":  "And say to him, \u0027Would you [be willing to] purify yourself"
                   },
                   {
                       "ayah":  19,
                       "arabic":  "وَأَهْدِيَكَ إِلَىٰ رَبِّكَ فَتَخْشَىٰ",
                       "english":  "And let me guide you to your Lord so you would fear [Him]?\u0027\""
                   },
                   {
                       "ayah":  20,
                       "arabic":  "فَأَرَىٰهُ ٱلْءَايَةَ ٱلْكُبْرَىٰ",
                       "english":  "And he showed him the greatest sign,"
                   },
                   {
                       "ayah":  21,
                       "arabic":  "فَكَذَّبَ وَعَصَىٰ",
                       "english":  "But Pharaoh denied and disobeyed."
                   },
                   {
                       "ayah":  22,
                       "arabic":  "ثُمَّ أَدْبَرَ يَسْعَىٰ",
                       "english":  "Then he turned his back, striving."
                   },
                   {
                       "ayah":  23,
                       "arabic":  "فَحَشَرَ فَنَادَىٰ",
                       "english":  "And he gathered [his people] and called out"
                   },
                   {
                       "ayah":  24,
                       "arabic":  "فَقَالَ أَنَا۠ رَبُّكُمُ ٱلْأَعْلَىٰ",
                       "english":  "And said, \"I am your most exalted lord.\""
                   },
                   {
                       "ayah":  25,
                       "arabic":  "فَأَخَذَهُ ٱللَّهُ نَكَالَ ٱلْءَاخِرَةِ وَٱلْأُولَىٰٓ",
                       "english":  "So Allah seized him in exemplary punishment for the last and the first [transgression]."
                   },
                   {
                       "ayah":  26,
                       "arabic":  "إِنَّ فِى ذَٰلِكَ لَعِبْرَةًۭ لِّمَن يَخْشَىٰٓ",
                       "english":  "Indeed in that is a warning for whoever would fear [Allah]."
                   },
                   {
                       "ayah":  27,
                       "arabic":  "ءَأَنتُمْ أَشَدُّ خَلْقًا أَمِ ٱلسَّمَآءُ ۚ بَنَىٰهَا",
                       "english":  "Are you a more difficult creation or is the heaven? Allah constructed it."
                   },
                   {
                       "ayah":  28,
                       "arabic":  "رَفَعَ سَمْكَهَا فَسَوَّىٰهَا",
                       "english":  "He raised its ceiling and proportioned it."
                   },
                   {
                       "ayah":  29,
                       "arabic":  "وَأَغْطَشَ لَيْلَهَا وَأَخْرَجَ ضُحَىٰهَا",
                       "english":  "And He darkened its night and extracted its brightness."
                   },
                   {
                       "ayah":  30,
                       "arabic":  "وَٱلْأَرْضَ بَعْدَ ذَٰلِكَ دَحَىٰهَآ",
                       "english":  "And after that He spread the earth."
                   },
                   {
                       "ayah":  31,
                       "arabic":  "أَخْرَجَ مِنْهَا مَآءَهَا وَمَرْعَىٰهَا",
                       "english":  "He extracted from it its water and its pasture,"
                   },
                   {
                       "ayah":  32,
                       "arabic":  "وَٱلْجِبَالَ أَرْسَىٰهَا",
                       "english":  "And the mountains He set firmly"
                   },
                   {
                       "ayah":  33,
                       "arabic":  "مَتَٰعًۭا لَّكُمْ وَلِأَنْعَٰمِكُمْ",
                       "english":  "As provision for you and your grazing livestock."
                   },
                   {
                       "ayah":  34,
                       "arabic":  "فَإِذَا جَآءَتِ ٱلطَّآمَّةُ ٱلْكُبْرَىٰ",
                       "english":  "But when there comes the greatest Overwhelming Calamity -"
                   },
                   {
                       "ayah":  35,
                       "arabic":  "يَوْمَ يَتَذَكَّرُ ٱلْإِنسَٰنُ مَا سَعَىٰ",
                       "english":  "The Day when man will remember that for which he strove,"
                   },
                   {
                       "ayah":  36,
                       "arabic":  "وَبُرِّزَتِ ٱلْجَحِيمُ لِمَن يَرَىٰ",
                       "english":  "And Hellfire will be exposed for [all] those who see -"
                   },
                   {
                       "ayah":  37,
                       "arabic":  "فَأَمَّا مَن طَغَىٰ",
                       "english":  "So as for he who transgressed"
                   },
                   {
                       "ayah":  38,
                       "arabic":  "وَءَاثَرَ ٱلْحَيَوٰةَ ٱلدُّنْيَا",
                       "english":  "And preferred the life of the world,"
                   },
                   {
                       "ayah":  39,
                       "arabic":  "فَإِنَّ ٱلْجَحِيمَ هِىَ ٱلْمَأْوَىٰ",
                       "english":  "Then indeed, Hellfire will be [his] refuge."
                   },
                   {
                       "ayah":  40,
                       "arabic":  "وَأَمَّا مَنْ خَافَ مَقَامَ رَبِّهِۦ وَنَهَى ٱلنَّفْسَ عَنِ ٱلْهَوَىٰ",
                       "english":  "But as for he who feared the position of his Lord and prevented the soul from [unlawful] inclination,"
                   },
                   {
                       "ayah":  41,
                       "arabic":  "فَإِنَّ ٱلْجَنَّةَ هِىَ ٱلْمَأْوَىٰ",
                       "english":  "Then indeed, Paradise will be [his] refuge."
                   },
                   {
                       "ayah":  42,
                       "arabic":  "يَسْـَٔلُونَكَ عَنِ ٱلسَّاعَةِ أَيَّانَ مُرْسَىٰهَا",
                       "english":  "They ask you, [O Muhammad], about the Hour: when is its arrival?"
                   },
                   {
                       "ayah":  43,
                       "arabic":  "فِيمَ أَنتَ مِن ذِكْرَىٰهَآ",
                       "english":  "In what [position] are you that you should mention it?"
                   },
                   {
                       "ayah":  44,
                       "arabic":  "إِلَىٰ رَبِّكَ مُنتَهَىٰهَآ",
                       "english":  "To your Lord is its finality."
                   },
                   {
                       "ayah":  45,
                       "arabic":  "إِنَّمَآ أَنتَ مُنذِرُ مَن يَخْشَىٰهَا",
                       "english":  "You are only a warner for those who fear it."
                   },
                   {
                       "ayah":  46,
                       "arabic":  "كَأَنَّهُمْ يَوْمَ يَرَوْنَهَا لَمْ يَلْبَثُوٓا۟ إِلَّا عَشِيَّةً أَوْ ضُحَىٰهَا",
                       "english":  "It will be, on the Day they see it, as though they had not remained [in the world] except for an afternoon or a morning thereof."
                   }
               ]
}